.TH HACKTRIX 1 "2026-05-13" "hacktrix" "Security Research Tools"
.SH NAME
hacktrix \- search HackTricks and PayloadsAllTheThings for exploitation techniques; generate CSRF PoC files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hacktrix
.B \-l
[
.B \-\-since
.I N[d]
]
.br
.B hacktrix
.B \-u
.br
.B hacktrix
.B \-f
.I TERM
[
.I TERM
\&...]
.br
.B hacktrix
.B \-p
.I TERM
[
.I TERM
\&...]
[
.B \-d
.I CONTEXT
]
.br
.B hacktrix
.B \-m
.I PATH
[
.B \-s
.I TERM
]
.br
.B hacktrix
.B \-\-csrf
.I FILE
[
.B \-\-bypass
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hacktrix
searches local clones of HackTricks and PayloadsAllTheThings (PATT) for
exploitation techniques matching all provided search terms.
.PP
Use
.B \-l
to browse all top\-level categories in both sources without search terms.
Use
.B \-u
to pull the latest commits from both knowledge bases and print a change summary.
Use
.B \-f
to browse matching entries as a clean table (fast, no API cost).
Use
.B \-p
to send the matching content to Claude and receive a single,
syntax\-highlighted, ready\-to\-use payload with a recommendation.
Feed back errors or context with
.B \-d
to get an adapted payload on the next attempt.
Use
.B \-m
to copy a file from a
.B \-f
result to the current directory as plain text with markdown stripped.
Optionally scope the output to a specific section with
.BR \-s .
.PP
Use
.B \-\-csrf
to parse a raw HTTP request file (Burp or Caido format) and generate a
self-contained CSRF proof-of-concept HTML file
.RI ( csrf_poc.html )
in the current directory.
The PoC type is selected automatically based on the request's Content-Type:
a form-urlencoded POST becomes an auto-submitting HTML form, a JSON POST
becomes a
.B fetch()
call, a GET becomes an
.B <img>
tag, and a multipart POST becomes a FormData skeleton.
No API call is made by default.
Add
.B \-\-bypass
to send the request metadata to Claude and receive token bypass techniques,
Content-Type attack notes, and up to four bypass variants with notes on how
to adapt the generated PoC.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-list
List all top\-level directories in both HackTricks and PayloadsAllTheThings.
No search terms needed. Use this to explore available categories before
narrowing down with
.BR \-f .
Each source prints a footer with its category count.
Combine with
.B \-\-since
to filter to recently updated categories.
.TP
.BR \-u ", " \-\-update
Run
.B git pull \-\-ff\-only
on both knowledge bases and print a per\-source change summary (files changed,
insertions, deletions). Use this to keep payloads current before an engagement.
.TP
.BR \-\-since " " \fIN[d]\fR
Optional. Use with
.B \-l
to filter the category list to directories that have had commits in the last
.I N
days (e.g.
.B \-\-since 7d
or
.BR \-\-since\ 7 ).
The footer shows how many categories matched out of the total.
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-find " " \fITERM\fR " [" \fITERM\fR ...]"
Search both sources for files containing all specified terms. Displays a
table with source tag, matched section title, and relative file path.
No Claude call is made. Fast and offline\-capable.
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-payload " " \fITERM\fR " [" \fITERM\fR ...]"
Search both sources for files containing all specified terms, then send
the matched content to Claude. Claude selects the single most impactful
payload, syntax\-highlights it by language (JavaScript, PHP, Groovy,
Bash, Python, Java), and provides a one\-line recommendation.
A raw copy\-paste block is printed below the highlighted view for safe terminal selection.
Requires
.BR ANTHROPIC_API_KEY .
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-mirror " " \fIPATH\fR
Copy a file to the current directory as plain text with markdown stripped.
.I PATH
is the relative path exactly as shown in a
.B \-f
result. Paths with spaces must be quoted. Shell alias:
.BR htm .
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-section " " \fITERM\fR
Optional. Use with
.B \-m
to extract only the section whose heading contains
.IR TERM .
Extracts from the matched heading down to the next heading of equal or
higher level. Falls back to the full file if no matching heading is found.
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-details " " \fICONTEXT\fR
Optional. Pass error output or additional context from a previous
.B \-p
attempt. Claude will analyse the failure and produce an adapted payload.
The output includes a
.B "What changed"
section listing the specific tokens or lines modified from the previous attempt.
Repeat
.B \-d
to chain multiple error contexts across attempts (e.g.
.BR "\-d \(dqerr1\(dq \-d \(dqerr2\(dq" ).
Only meaningful with
.BR \-p .
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-log
Skip auto\-logging this
.B \-p
result to
.IR ~/Tools/hacktrix-session.log .
By default every
.B \-p
call appends a timestamped entry (terms, vulnerability, first payload line) to that log.
.TP
.BR \-\-csrf " " \fIFILE\fR
Parse a raw HTTP request file and generate a self-contained CSRF PoC HTML
file saved as
.I csrf_poc.html
in the current directory.
.I FILE
should be a plain-text file containing the raw request as copied from Burp
Suite or Caido (request line, headers, blank line, optional body).
The PoC type is selected by Content-Type:
.RS
.IP \(bu 4
form-urlencoded \(em auto-submitting HTML
.B <form>
with hidden inputs
.IP \(bu 4
application/json \(em
.B fetch()
call with
.B credentials: 'include'
and a CORS note
.IP \(bu 4
multipart/form-data \(em
.B FormData
.B fetch()
skeleton (fields must be filled manually)
.IP \(bu 4
GET \(em
.B <img>
tag for zero-click delivery
.RE
.RS
No API call is made. Field names, values, and the target URL are HTML-escaped
in the generated output.
.RE
.TP
.BR \-\-bypass
Optional. Use with
.B \-\-csrf
to send the request metadata to Claude and receive a bypass analysis:
CSRF token detection, Content-Type attack suggestions, and up to four bypass
variants with PoC adaptation notes.
Requires
.BR ANTHROPIC_API_KEY .
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
Required when using
.BR \-p " / " \-\-payload
or
.BR \-\-bypass .
Obtain from console.anthropic.com.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/Tools/hacktricks
Local clone of the HackTricks knowledge base.
Clone with:
.B git clone https://github.com/HackTricks\-wiki/hacktricks ~/Tools/hacktricks
.TP
.I ~/Tools/payloadsallthethings
Local clone of PayloadsAllTheThings.
Clone with:
.B git clone https://github.com/swisskyrepo/PayloadsAllTheThings ~/Tools/payloadsallthethings
.SH EXAMPLES
Browse categories (update sources first):
.PP
.RS
.nf
hacktrix \-u
hacktrix \-l
hacktrix \-l \-\-since 7d
.fi
.RE
.PP
Browse matching entries before committing to a payload:
.PP
.RS
.nf
hacktrix \-f ssti handlebars
hacktrix \-f lfi php windows iis
.fi
.RE
.PP
Generate a payload directly:
.PP
.RS
.nf
hacktrix \-p ssti handlebars groovy rce
hacktrix \-p sqli union mysql
hacktrix \-p xss csp bypass reflected
hacktrix \-p lfi php windows iis read
.fi
.RE
.PP
Adapt after a failed attempt:
.PP
.RS
.nf
hacktrix \-p ssti handlebars groovy rce \-d "'require' is not defined"
hacktrix \-p sqli union mysql \-d "WAF blocking SELECT and UNION keywords"
hacktrix \-p lfi php \-d "../etc/passwd filtered, server returned 403"
.fi
.RE
.PP
Mirror a file from a \-f result (full file):
.PP
.RS
.nf
htm "Server Side Template Injection/JavaScript.md"
.fi
.RE
.PP
Mirror a specific section only:
.PP
.RS
.nf
htm "Server Side Template Injection/JavaScript.md" \-s handlebars
htm "File Inclusion/README.md" \-s php
.fi
.RE
.PP
Generate a CSRF PoC from a captured request:
.PP
.RS
.nf
hacktrix \-\-csrf req.txt                   # offline PoC, no API cost
hacktrix \-\-csrf req.txt \-\-bypass          # PoC + Claude bypass analysis
.fi
.RE
.PP
Typical workflow:
.PP
.RS
.nf
hacktrix \-u                                                        # keep sources current
hacktrix \-l \-\-since 7d                                             # browse recent updates
hacktrix \-f ssti handlebars                                        # see what files match
htm "Server Side Template Injection/JavaScript.md" \-s handlebars   # grab the section
hacktrix \-p ssti handlebars groovy                                  # generate a payload
hacktrix \-p ssti handlebars groovy \-d "'require' is not defined"    # adapt after error
.fi
.RE
.SH NOTES
All search terms are AND\-matched against file content (case\-insensitive).
More specific terms return fewer files and produce more focused payloads.
If
.B \-p
returns no results, drop a term and try again.
.PP
Each
.B \-p
call costs approximately $0.001\(en$0.005 in Claude API credits
(claude\-sonnet\-4\-6, ~200\(en500 tokens output).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR searchsploit (1),
.BR msfconsole (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Written by jhaxx.
